Build ID: Version: 3.3.1.1
Steps To Reproduce: 1. Start a new project. 2. Goto Team menu and select Share project 3. Select server and module to checkout. 4. When you click next after "Select Tag" step all files are downloaded and compare to the empty project, why is there no option to save those files directly?
More information: (Same thing on linux)

Fredrik, I'm not sure what did you mean by "files are downloaded", afaik no such thing happen while sharing a project. Also, could you explain to me what did you mean by "save files directly"?
The page you're referring to allows the user to select which resources should or shouldn't be committed.

When you have selected module and tag from a reposatory (ex. CVS)
The detail box says it's downloading the files from the reposatory and the it says it compares them. After this you come to the last screen in the "Share Wizard" called Commit wizard (if I remember correctly) where it says that all files from the reposatory are new. This is more apparent if you download a large project into a new eclipse project, I downloaded the CDT source from the web reposatory.
As the files are downloaded to make the compares to detect which files are new/conflict/aren't in the reposatory before getting to the Commit Wizard, I would prefer a option to save the files that are downloaded for the compare.

Created attachment 87087 say download after selecting next from select tag
Created attachment 87088 download and compare complete (optional select wizard)

Frederik, thanks for the additional info. I didn't realize that you were talking about a project that already exists in a repository. If I understood the issue you are referring to correctly, I belive the answer might be to deselect the "Launch the Commit Wizard" option from the "Share Project Resources" page on the wizard. This way, after clicking "Finish" button the wizard will be closed and you'll end up with a shared project with all the new file marked as unshared. You will need to synchronize the project in order to see what file are out-dated, conflicting and so. How does it sound?
The process looks a little bit different when there is a CVS meta information in the project you're sharing, but doesn't seem to be your case.

The problem is not to skip the commit wizard and download the source
The problems is that in image "say download after selecting next from select tag" it says it's downloading all files to do the initial compare. So why is there no option to save those files that are downloaded for the compare?

I'm going to jump in here and make some comments. First of all, it seems strange to me that you are using the Share Project wizard to perform a checkout. Is there some reason why you are not using the Checkout wizard (available from the File/Import menu)? The reason we don't automatically checkout the contents into the workspace is because a Share operation was intended to be a way to put content on the server, not to get server content onto your local machine. You can use the last page of the Sharing wizard to get the contents but, as you indicated, this fetches the content again. The previously fetched contents are cached so it would be possible to modify the Sharing wizard to provide an option to use the cached contents instead of contacting the server but, given that this is a non-standard workflow and is not something that is done on a daily basis, I wouldn't give this a high priority. Of course, those who have differing opinions are welcome to provide a patch ;-)

OK, I never know/used the import button.
So a follow up question then, why doesn't the import option appear in the Team menu for a project?
Because the import operation creates projects (i.e. that is a similar question to "why doesn't the New Project option appear in the content menu of a project").
But there is a option to import to a existing project.

(In reply to comment #11) > But there is a option to import to a existing project.
Fredrik, could you explain which option did you mean? Also, can you confirm that Checkout wizard mentioned by Michael solves the problem?
